
                                                                 *read-base*


    VARIABLE
    *read-base*  -  the radix in which integers and ratios are read

    USAGE
    *read-base*

    DESCRIPTION
    Bound to the integer that is the current radix  in  which  integers  and
    ratios are read.  The allowable values are from 2 to 36, inclusive.

    EXAMPLES
    ;;  Assume the value of *PRINT-BASE* is ten.
    *read-base* => 10
    (setq *read-base* 12)
    12 => 14

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 22:344, *print-base*, read












































